#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:1
msgid "The (future of the) Black code style"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:3
msgid "Preview style"
msgstr "預覽風格"

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:7
msgid ""
"Experimental, potentially disruptive style changes are gathered under the `--"
"preview` CLI flag. At the end of each year, these changes may be adopted "
"into the default style, as described in [The Black Code Style](index.md). "
"Because the functionality is experimental, feedback and issue reports are "
"highly encouraged!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:14
msgid "Currently, the following features are included in the preview style:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:16
msgid ""
"`wrap_comprehension_in`: Wrap the `in` clause of list and dictionary "
"comprehensions across lines if it would otherwise exceed the maximum line "
"length. ([see below](labels/wrap-comprehension-in))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:19
msgid ""
"`simplify_power_operator_hugging`: Use a simpler implementation of the power "
"operator \"hugging\" logic (removing whitespace around `**` in simple "
"expressions), which applies also in the rare case the exponentiation is "
"split into separate lines. ([see below](labels/simplify-power-operator))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:23
msgid ""
"`wrap_long_dict_values_in_parens`: Add parentheses around long values in "
"dictionaries. ([see below](labels/wrap-long-dict-values))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:25
msgid ""
"`fix_if_guard_explosion_in_case_statement`: fixed exploding of the if guard "
"in case patterns which have trailing commas in them, even if the guard "
"expression fits in one line"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:28
msgid ""
"`pyi_overload_group_blank_lines`: In `.pyi` stub files, improve heuristics "
"around when blank lines should appear before, after and within decorated "
"function groups. ([see below](labels/pyi-overload-group))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:31
msgid ""
"`pyi_blank_line_before_decorated_class`: In `.pyi` stub files, enforce a "
"blank line before a decorated class definition when it follows a function "
"definition. ([see below](labels/pyi-blank-line-before-decorated-class))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:34
msgid ""
"`hug_comparator`: Don't break a comparator (`not in`, `==`, `is`, ...) away "
"from its left operand when the right operand is a bracketed expression that "
"has to break anyway; let the bracket explode instead. ([see below](labels/"
"hug-comparator))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:40
msgid "Wrapping long comprehension `in` clauses"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:42
msgid ""
"When a list or dictionary comprehension has a long `in` clause that would "
"exceed the maximum line length, Black will wrap it across multiple lines for "
"better readability. This helps keep comprehensions readable when the "
"iterable expression is complex or lengthy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:47
#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:99
msgid "For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:49
msgid ""
"# Before\n"
"result = [\n"
"    very_very_very_very_very_long_item\n"
"    for very_very_very_very_very_long_item in "
"some_very_very_very_very_very_very_long_function_name\n"
"]\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:57
#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:79
msgid "will be formatted to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:59
msgid ""
"# After\n"
"result = [\n"
"    very_very_very_very_very_long_item\n"
"    for very_very_very_very_very_long_item in (\n"
"        some_very_very_very_very_very_very_long_function_name\n"
"    )\n"
"]\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:69
msgid "This also applies to dictionary comprehensions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:71
msgid ""
"# Before\n"
"mapping = {\n"
"    very_long_key: very_very_very_long_item\n"
"    for very_long_key, very_very_very_long_item in "
"very_very_very_very_long_function_name\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:81
msgid ""
"# After\n"
"mapping = {\n"
"    very_long_key: very_very_very_long_item\n"
"    for very_long_key, very_very_very_long_item in (\n"
"        very_very_very_very_long_function_name\n"
"    )\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:93
msgid "Simplified power operator whitespace handling"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:95
msgid ""
"Black's power operator \"hugging\" logic removes whitespace around `**` in "
"simple expressions (e.g., `x**2` instead of `x ** 2`). This feature uses a "
"simpler, more consistent implementation that also applies when "
"exponentiation is split across lines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:101
msgid ""
"# Simple expressions - whitespace is removed\n"
"result = x**2 + y**3\n"
"value = base**exponent\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:107
msgid ""
"When the exponentiation is split across lines (rare), the simplified logic "
"ensures consistent formatting:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:110
msgid ""
"# Complex expression split across lines\n"
"result = (\n"
"    some_very_long_base_expression\n"
"    **some_very_long_exponent_expression\n"
"    **some_very_long_third_expression\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:119
msgid ""
"This feature primarily improves the internal consistency of Black's "
"formatting logic rather than making dramatic visual changes to most code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:124
msgid "Improved parentheses management in dicts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:126
msgid ""
"For dict literals with long values, they are now wrapped in parentheses. "
"Unnecessary parentheses are now removed. For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:129
msgid ""
"my_dict = {\n"
"    \"a key in my dict\": a_very_long_variable\n"
"    * and_a_very_long_function_call()\n"
"    / 100000.0,\n"
"    \"another key\": (short_value),\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
"my_dict = {\n"
"    \"a key in my dict\": a_very_long_variable\n"
"    * and_a_very_long_function_call()\n"
"    / 100000.0,\n"
"    \"another key\": (short_value),\n"
"}\n"

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:138
#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:366
msgid "will be changed to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:140
msgid ""
"my_dict = {\n"
"    \"a key in my dict\": (\n"
"        a_very_long_variable * and_a_very_long_function_call() / 100000.0\n"
"    ),\n"
"    \"another key\": short_value,\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
"my_dict = {\n"
"    \"a key in my dict\": (\n"
"        a_very_long_variable * and_a_very_long_function_call() / 100000.0\n"
"    ),\n"
"    \"another key\": short_value,\n"
"}\n"

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:151
msgid "Improved overload groups in stub files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:153
msgid ""
"In `.pyi` stub files, Black now has improved heuristics regarding when blank "
"lines should appear before, after or within groups of decorated functions "
"that share the same name (such as `@overload` groups). Two rules are applied "
"when a decorated function is determined to be part of a series of >=2 "
"decorated functions with the same name:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:158
msgid ""
"**Before the decorated function**: a blank line is always inserted, unless "
"the preceding statement is a same-name decorated function (i.e. part of an "
"`@overload` group) or the function is the first statement in its block."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:161
msgid ""
"**After the decorated function**: a blank line is always inserted, unless "
"the following statement is a same-name decorated function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:164
msgid ""
"These rules apply regardless of what the adjacent statement is — whether "
"it's another function definition, a variable annotation, or any other "
"statement."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:167
msgid ""
"Previously, Black could insert unwanted blank lines _within_ an overload "
"group when one of the overloads had a docstring, and did not consistently "
"enforce blank lines at the boundaries of overload groups:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:171
msgid ""
"# Before\n"
"\n"
"@overload\n"
"def foo(x: int) -> int:\n"
"    \"\"\"Docs.\"\"\"\n"
"\n"
"@overload                    # unwanted blank line within group\n"
"def foo(x: str) -> str: ...\n"
"def bar(x): ...              # no blank line after group\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:183
msgid ""
"With this feature enabled, the group is kept together and clearly separated "
"from surrounding code:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:186
msgid ""
"# After (with --preview)\n"
"\n"
"@overload\n"
"def foo(x: int) -> int:\n"
"    \"\"\"Docs.\"\"\"\n"
"@overload\n"
"def foo(x: str) -> str: ...\n"
"\n"
"def bar(x): ...\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:200
msgid "Blank line before decorated classes in stub files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:202
msgid ""
"In `.pyi` stub files, Black already enforces blank lines around class "
"definitions in many situations. However, when a class has a decorator, Black "
"previously failed to enforce this, instead _removing_ the blank line between "
"a function and the decorator:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:206
msgid ""
"  # Before\n"
"\n"
"  def foo(): ...\n"
"-\n"
"  @decorator\n"
"  class Bar: ...\n"
"\n"
"  def baz(): ...\n"
"  @decorator\n"
"  class Spam: ...\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:219
msgid ""
"With this feature enabled, a blank line is enforced, consistent with how "
"undecorated classes are handled:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:222
msgid ""
"  # After (with --preview)\n"
"\n"
"  def foo(): ...\n"
"\n"
"  @decorator\n"
"  class Bar: ...\n"
"\n"
"  def baz(): ...\n"
"+\n"
"  @decorator\n"
"  class Spam: ...\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:238
msgid "Keep comparators next to their left operand"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:240
msgid ""
"When a comparator (`not in`, `==`, `is`, ...) sits inside another bracketed "
"construct and its right operand is a bracketed expression that has to break "
"(either via a magic trailing comma or because the line is too long), Black "
"used to split the line right before the comparator. The left operand ended "
"up alone on its own line, visually disconnected from the operator and the "
"operand that explains it:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:246
msgid ""
"# Before\n"
"\n"
"x = [\n"
"    t\n"
"    for t in y\n"
"    if t\n"
"    not in {\n"
"        LongNameOne,\n"
"        LongNameTwo,\n"
"        LongNameThree,\n"
"    }\n"
"]\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:261
msgid ""
"With this feature enabled, Black skips that comparator split and lets the "
"right-hand bracket explode instead, which it would have done anyway:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:264
msgid ""
"# After (with --preview)\n"
"\n"
"x = [\n"
"    t\n"
"    for t in y\n"
"    if t not in {\n"
"        LongNameOne,\n"
"        LongNameTwo,\n"
"        LongNameThree,\n"
"    }\n"
"]\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:278
msgid ""
"The fix is not limited to comprehensions. The same shape appears inside `if`/"
"`elif` chains, `assert` statements, and parenthesized expressions, and gets "
"the same treatment:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:281
msgid ""
"# Before\n"
"\n"
"if (\n"
"    is_scalar(value)\n"
"    and self.dtype\n"
"    in (np.dtype(\"float64\"), np.dtype(\"float32\"), np.dtype(\"object\"))\n"
"    and (limit is not None or inplace)\n"
"):\n"
"    ...\n"
"\n"
"assert (\n"
"    bool\n"
"    is _AnnotationExtractor(attr.fields(C).x.converter.__call__)."
"get_return_type()\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:298
msgid ""
"# After (with --preview)\n"
"\n"
"if (\n"
"    is_scalar(value)\n"
"    and self.dtype in (\n"
"        np.dtype(\"float64\"),\n"
"        np.dtype(\"float32\"),\n"
"        np.dtype(\"object\"),\n"
"    )\n"
"    and (limit is not None or inplace)\n"
"):\n"
"    ...\n"
"\n"
"assert (\n"
"    bool is _AnnotationExtractor(\n"
"        attr.fields(C).x.converter.__call__\n"
"    ).get_return_type()\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:319
msgid "Unstable style"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:323
msgid ""
"In the past, the preview style included some features with known bugs, so "
"that we were unable to move these features to the stable style. Therefore, "
"such features are now moved to the `--unstable` style. All features in the "
"`--preview` style are expected to make it to next year's stable style; "
"features in the `--unstable` style will be stabilized only if issues with "
"them are fixed. If bugs are discovered in a `--preview` feature, it is "
"demoted to the `--unstable` style. To avoid thrash when a feature is demoted "
"from the `--preview` to the `--unstable` style, users can use the `--enable-"
"unstable-feature` flag to enable specific unstable features."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:334
msgid "The unstable style additionally includes the following features:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:336
msgid ""
"`hug_parens_with_braces_and_square_brackets`: More compact formatting of "
"nested brackets. ([see below](labels/hug-parens))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:338
msgid ""
"`string_processing`: Split long string literals and related changes. ([see "
"below](labels/string-processing))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:343
msgid ""
"Improved multiline dictionary and list indentation for sole function "
"parameter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:345
msgid ""
"For better readability and less verticality, _Black_ now pairs parentheses "
"(\"(\", \")\") with braces (\"{\", \"}\") and square brackets (\"[\", \"]\") "
"on the same line. For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:348
msgid ""
"foo(\n"
"    [\n"
"        1,\n"
"        2,\n"
"        3,\n"
"    ]\n"
")\n"
"\n"
"nested_array = [\n"
"    [\n"
"        1,\n"
"        2,\n"
"        3,\n"
"    ]\n"
"]\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:368
msgid ""
"foo([\n"
"    1,\n"
"    2,\n"
"    3,\n"
"])\n"
"\n"
"nested_array = [[\n"
"    1,\n"
"    2,\n"
"    3,\n"
"]]\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:382
msgid "This also applies to list and dictionary unpacking:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:384
msgid ""
"foo(\n"
"    *[\n"
"        a_long_function_name(a_long_variable_name)\n"
"        for a_long_variable_name in some_generator\n"
"    ]\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:393
msgid "will become:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:395
msgid ""
"foo(*[\n"
"    a_long_function_name(a_long_variable_name)\n"
"    for a_long_variable_name in some_generator\n"
"])\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:402
msgid ""
"You can use a magic trailing comma to avoid this compacting behavior; by "
"default, _Black_ will not reformat the following code:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:405
msgid ""
"foo(\n"
"    [\n"
"        1,\n"
"        2,\n"
"        3,\n"
"    ],\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:417
msgid "Improved string processing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/future_style.md:419
msgid ""
"_Black_ will split long string literals and merge short ones. Parentheses "
"are used where appropriate. When split, parts of f-strings that don't need "
"formatting are converted to plain strings. f-strings will not be merged if "
"they contain internal quotes and it would change their quotation mark style. "
"Line continuation backslashes are converted into parenthesized strings. "
"Unnecessary parentheses are stripped. The stability and status of this "
"feature is tracked in [this issue](https://github.com/psf/black/issues/2188)."
msgstr ""
